description:
secretx-core/src/lib.rs:1416-1457: get_blocking builds 'tokio::runtime::Builder::new_current_thread().enable_all().build().map_err(|e| SecretError::Backend{ backend:"blocking", source: e.into() })?.block_on(store.get())' twice — once on the no-runtime branch, once inside the spawned scoped thread on the existing-runtime branch. Same code, different indentation.

Suggested refactor:
    fn build_one_shot_runtime() -> Result<tokio::runtime::Runtime, SecretError> {
        tokio::runtime::Builder::new_current_thread()
            .enable_all()
            .build()
            .map_err(|e| SecretError::Backend {
                backend: "blocking",
                source: e.into(),
            })
    }
Then both branches call build_one_shot_runtime()?.block_on(...). Same shape as run_on_new_thread (lib.rs:1370-1377) which does the same boilerplate a third time.

Note: this is a polish fix, not urgent. The duplication is short and obvious; a contributor reading either branch can follow it. P3.
